questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;No Error&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence structure is correct, with a main clause (&amp;quot;I hope that&amp;quot;) and a subordinate clause (&amp;quot;we will arrive at the ideal trade-off soon&amp;quot;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Verb tenses and prepositions are correctly used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Noun phrase and adverb are correctly positioned and used in the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option 3&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at each part of the sentence&lt;/strong&gt;:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;I hope that&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is grammatically sound. The verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;hope&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is correctly complemented by the connector &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;that,&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;which introduces a subordinate clause expressing the content of the hope.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;we will arrive at&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;does not contain any grammatical mistakes. The future tense &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;will arrive&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is appropriate because the speaker is expressing a hope about a future event. The preposition &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;at&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is correctly used as well, since &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;arrive at&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is a standard phrase meaning to reach a decision or an agreement.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the ideal trade-off soon&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is also grammatically correct. The noun phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the ideal trade-off&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is a suitable object for the clause, indicated by the definite article &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;the,&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;the adjective &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;ideal,&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;and the compound noun &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;trade-off.&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;The adverb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;soon&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;correctly modifies the verb phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;will arrive at,&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;indicating when the speaker hopes the action will take place.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The erroneous part is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in &lt;strong&gt;part B&lt;/strong&gt; of the given sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Meaning of &lt;strong&gt;later&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;refers to a time in the future.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Right now I&amp;rsquo;m giving you a lesson, and I&amp;rsquo;ll go to the gym &lt;strong&gt;later&lt;/strong&gt;, meaning in the evening, in the future from this moment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Meaning of &lt;strong&gt;latter&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (68, 68, 68);  &quot;&gt;This is used when you mention two things, and then you want to refer back specifically to the second thing.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (68, 68, 68);  &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;There are two kinds of worries: those you can do something about and those you can&amp;rsquo;t. Don&amp;rsquo;t spend any time on the &lt;strong&gt;latter&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (68, 68, 68);  &quot;&gt;Therefore in the given sentence &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;later&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be replaced with &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;latter&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (68, 68, 68);  &quot;&gt;This is because the &lt;strong&gt;jute&lt;/strong&gt; which is&amp;nbsp;the &lt;strong&gt;second thing&lt;/strong&gt; mentioned is preferred.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (68, 68, 68);  &quot;&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (68, 68, 68);  &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct sentence is:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;When there is an option between the plastic and jute, the &lt;strong&gt;latter&lt;/strong&gt; is doubtlessly the better&amp;nbsp;choice.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The erroneous part is: &lt;strong&gt;A soothe voice&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the second&amp;nbsp;part of the given sentence, the&amp;nbsp;phrase&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;A soothe voice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;incorrect&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct phrase should be&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;A soothing voice&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; as&amp;nbsp;the &lt;strong&gt;adjective&lt;/strong&gt; form &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;soothing&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is needed here.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;adjective&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;soothing&amp;#39; is used to describe the &lt;strong&gt;noun&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;voice&amp;#39; in the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, it should be corrected to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;A soothing voice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to properly convey the intended meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;soothing&lt;/strong&gt; voice must convey both confidence and intimacy, qualities which can be attributed to a few key components&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is-&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;(B).&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part (B)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We use the conjunction&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unless&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to mean&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;except if.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i class=&quot;ti&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ruby druby&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; display: inline-block;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;rb drb&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;&quot;&gt;They won&amp;rsquo;t come&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;tb&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unless&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;ruby druby&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; display: inline-block;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;rb drb&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;&quot;&gt;you invite them&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Alt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;hough&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;in spite of something.&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is a subordinating conjunction.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This means that the clause which they introduce is a subordinate clause, which needs a main clause to make it complete.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;although&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;clause comes after the main clause, it can also mean&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;but it is also true that &amp;hellip;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;We didn&amp;rsquo;t make any profit&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;al&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;though&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;nobody knows why.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the use of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;unless&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;should be replaced by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;although&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to make it grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;(B).&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;It hardly oozes charm now, &lt;strong&gt;although&lt;/strong&gt; there have been a few attempts to gentrify it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;conjunction&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a joiner, a word that connects (conjoins) parts of a sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Coordinating conjunctions&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;join equals to one another.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Most children like sweets&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;cookies.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Coordinating conjunctions go in between items joined, not at the beginning or end.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I like coffee,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;but&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;I don&amp;#39;t like tea.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;त्रुटि वाक्य के&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part (B)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;में है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Unless&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;हम conjunction&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unless&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;का&amp;nbsp;अर्थ&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;except if&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;हैं।
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i class=&quot;ti&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ruby druby&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; display: inline-block;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;rb drb&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;&quot;&gt;They won&amp;rsquo;t come&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;tb&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;unless&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;ruby druby&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; display: inline-block;&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;rb drb&quot; style=&quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;&quot;&gt;you invite them&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Alt&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;hough&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;का मतलब है &amp;#39;कुछ के बावजूद।&amp;#39;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;यह एक subordinating conjunction है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसका अर्थ यह है कि वे जिस clause&amp;nbsp;का परिचय देते हैं वह एक subordinate clause&amp;nbsp;है, जिसे पूरा करने के लिए एक main clause की आवश्यकता होती है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;जब main clause के बाद&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;although&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;उपवाक्य आता है, तो इसका अर्थ यह भी हो सकता है कि &amp;#39;लेकिन यह भी सत्य है कि...&amp;#39;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;We didn&amp;rsquo;t make any profit al&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;though&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;nobody knows why.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;इसलिए वाक्य&amp;nbsp;में&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;unless&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;के प्रयोग को&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;although&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;से बदल देना चाहिए ताकि वह व्याकरण की दृष्टि से सही हो।​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;Option 4:&lt;strong&gt; My research focus on&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The part &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;My research focus on&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is incorrect because the subject&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;research&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is singular, so it requires the singular form of the verb &amp;#39;focuses&amp;#39; rather than the plural &amp;#39;focus.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Replacing &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;focus&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; with&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;focuses&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;will correct the sentence, making it: &amp;quot;My research focuses on marine mammal behaviour, ecology, and conservation.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;This now-correct sentence means that the person&amp;#39;s research is specifically directed towards the behavior, ecology, and conservation of marine mammals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence&amp;#39;s grammar accurately communicates the research&amp;#39;s primary concerns.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the&lt;strong&gt; correct sentence &lt;/strong&gt;is:-&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;My research focuses on marine mammal behaviour, ecology and conservation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;ecology and conservation.&amp;#39; is grammatically correct. No changes needed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;marine mammal behaviour,&amp;#39; is also grammatically correct. No changes needed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;undergraduate days were&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;undergraduate days was&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; should be used instead of &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;undergraduate days were&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;One of the&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is followed by a &lt;strong&gt;plural noun&lt;/strong&gt; and a &lt;strong&gt;singular helping verb&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: One of the girls &lt;strong&gt;was &lt;/strong&gt;playing tennis.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct verb to use in this case should be &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;was&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; which is singular.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;One of the major challenges he faced during his &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;undergraduate days was&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;the shortage of money.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;A&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;error&lt;/strong&gt; lies in the &lt;strong&gt;first&lt;/strong&gt; part of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;has&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; (singular helping verb) is &lt;strong&gt;incorrect&lt;/strong&gt; here as it is used for &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;schools&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; (plural noun).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The helping verb &amp;#39;has&amp;#39; must be replaced with &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;have&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; to make the sentence grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct sentence is:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;Schools have been closed for almost a year and the students, especially those living in nearby slums, are struggling to focus on studies as they don&amp;rsquo;t have a personal and peaceful space to study.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;​Hence, the correct option is &lt;b&gt;A&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;i.e.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;respect those&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;has an error&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;respect those&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is incorrect because it implies that &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;those&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is necessary, which it is not.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In context, the sentence should simply be &amp;quot;Everyone should respect parents, teachers, and elders&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt; without the word &amp;quot;those.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Using &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;those&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; unnecessarily complicates the sentence and makes it awkward.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Correcting the sentence improves its readability and clarity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Everyone should respect parents, teachers, and elders&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1 (&amp;quot;and elders.&amp;quot;)&lt;/strong&gt; is correct as it is appropriately punctuated and completes the list.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2 (&amp;quot;parents, teachers,&amp;quot;) &lt;/strong&gt;is correct as it appropriately lists the nouns in the series.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4 (&amp;quot;Everyone should,&amp;quot;)&lt;/strong&gt; is correct as the introductory phrase of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The part of the sentence that contains a &lt;strong&gt;grammatical error&lt;/strong&gt; is:&lt;strong&gt; into Indian equities have pushed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;error in this sentence is related to &lt;/strong&gt;subject-verb agreement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;subject of the sentence&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;The inflow of foreign portfolio funds&amp;quot; is&lt;strong&gt; singular&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, it should be &lt;strong&gt;followed by &lt;/strong&gt;a &lt;strong&gt;singular verb&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;quot;has&amp;quot; &lt;strong&gt;instead of the&lt;/strong&gt; plural &amp;quot;have&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the&lt;strong&gt; corrected sentence&lt;/strong&gt; is: &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;The inflow of foreign portfolio funds&lt;strong&gt; into Indian equities has pushed &lt;/strong&gt;up price-earning multiples and valuation.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

The correct answer is: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;There were a time&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error is in subject-verb agreement as &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;time&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is a singular noun.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subject-verb agreement&lt;/strong&gt; is a grammatical rule that dictates that the verb in a sentence must agree in number with its subject.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The form of the verb should match the number of the subject.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct verb form for a singular subject &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;time&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;was&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; and not &amp;#39;were&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct sentence should be &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;There was a time&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; instead of &amp;#39;There were a time&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence should be written as &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;There was a time when scientists took this myth seriously&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The option that correctly rectifies the error in the given sentence is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;4&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;i.e.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;An innovative&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The original phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;a more innovative movie&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is incorrect. The correct phrase should be &amp;quot;an innovative movie&amp;quot;:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;The film received critical acclaim for being an innovative movie of the year.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The other options do not address the main error:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1:&lt;/strong&gt; Film receives &amp;ndash; changes the tense, which is unnecessary.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2:&lt;/strong&gt; In the year. &amp;ndash; does not correct the article error.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3:&lt;/strong&gt; Acclaim at &amp;ndash; changes the preposition, which is unnecessary.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;his team were not&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the &lt;strong&gt;subject-verb&lt;/strong&gt; agreement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this sentence, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;his team&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is the subject, which is a &lt;strong&gt;collective noun&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When a &lt;strong&gt;collective noun&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a &lt;strong&gt;single entity or unit&lt;/strong&gt;, it should be treated as &lt;strong&gt;singular&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the verb should be singular to match the subject.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;corrected sentence&lt;/strong&gt; should read:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The coach believed that his team was not playing to its potential in the tournament.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This maintains the correct subject-verb agreement, with &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;was&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; matching the singular subject &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;his team&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The primary issue in the sentence is the incorrect verb form &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;win&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; in the phrase &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;so he win easily&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct form should be &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;won&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; to match the present simple tense for third-person singular subjects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The revised phrase should be &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;so he won easily&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; ensuring grammatical correctness and clarity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, the error is located in &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;Paul and I played tennis yesterday. He&amp;rsquo;s much better than me, so he &lt;strong&gt;won&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;easily.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;pack&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct term when referring to multiple keys together is usually &amp;quot;set,&amp;quot; not &amp;quot;pack.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the phrase should be &amp;quot;a set of keys&amp;quot; instead of &amp;quot;a pack of keys.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The term &amp;quot;set&amp;quot; is commonly used to talk about a collection of related or similar items, such as keys, that are meant to be used together.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;quot;pack&amp;quot; is more commonly used for items that are bundled or wrapped together, like a pack of cards or a pack of gum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer&amp;nbsp;is &amp;quot;option 4&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;(c).&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Noncount (or uncountable) nouns (&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;work, air, bread, advice, news, information, education, etc&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;)&amp;nbsp;exist as masses or abstract quantities that cannot be counted.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;गैर-गणना (या बेशुमार) संज्ञाएं&amp;nbsp;(&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;work, air, bread, advice, news, information, education, etc&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;)&amp;nbsp;द्रव्यमान या अमूर्त मात्रा के रूप में मौजूद हैं जिन्हें गिना नहीं जा सकता।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They have no plural form.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;उनका कोई बहुवचन रूप नहीं है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Noncount nouns take a &lt;strong&gt;singular verb&lt;/strong&gt;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;गैर-गणना संज्ञा के साथ&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;singular verb&lt;/span&gt; का प्रयोग होता हैं।​
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Education is the key to success.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​​Hence, a singular helping verb&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;was&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;must be used in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part (c)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the use of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;were&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part (c)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence should be replaced with&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;was&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to make it grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;(c).&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​The correct sentence:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The information obtained from the business owners &lt;strong&gt;was&lt;/strong&gt; relevant to include in the study.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;helping verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(also known as an auxiliary verb) is used with a main verb to help express the main verb&amp;#39;s tense, mood, or voice.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;एक&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;helping verb&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;(जिसे auxiliary verb के रूप में भी जाना जाता है) का उपयोग मुख्य क्रिया के साथ मुख्य क्रिया के काल, मनोदशा या आवाज को व्यक्त करने में मदद के लिए किया जाता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The main helping verbs are&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;to be,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;to have,&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;to do.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They appear in the following forms:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;To Be: am, is, are, was, were, being, been, will be&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;To Have: has, have, had, having, will have.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Peter &lt;b&gt;has been&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;singing for an hour.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;c&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error is in the &lt;strong&gt;part c&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;here &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;lend&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be used instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;use&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Lend&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means to give something to someone for a short period of time, expecting it to be given back.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;If you need a coat i can &lt;strong&gt;lend&lt;/strong&gt; you one.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;lend&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be used in place of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;use&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct sentence is:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;I could not find my tennis racket so I asked Mani to &lt;strong&gt;lend&lt;/strong&gt; hers.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/confusion-points-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Confusion Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;Use&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;cannot be used in the given sentence as &amp;#39;use&amp;#39; means to take advantage of a person or situation, to exploit. It means to reduce the amount of or finish something, by eating it, burning it, writing on it, or by chemical reaction.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For example:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Does she still &lt;strong&gt;use &lt;/strong&gt;drugs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It might be possible to &lt;strong&gt;use&lt;/strong&gt; their mistake to help us to get what we want.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The erroneous part of the sentence&amp;nbsp;is: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;eleven to get of the last two.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;eleven to get of the last two&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is grammatically &lt;strong&gt;incorrect&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Of&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is used to show a relationship or connection between someone or something to another.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Off&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means away from someone or something, i.e. it expresses the act detachment from a person, place or object.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct phrase should be &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;eleven to get off the last two&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; to indicate the number of runs required to win. (Hindi: जीतने के लिए चाहिए होने वाले गेंदों की संख्या)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For example-&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;They needed eleven runs to get off the last two deliveries.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corrected sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;He belted two huge sixers, but eleven to get &lt;strong&gt;off &lt;/strong&gt;the last two deliveries was a big ask.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 2:&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Deliveries was a big ask&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;This part of the sentence is also &lt;strong&gt;grammatically correct&lt;/strong&gt;. It refers to the difficult task of scoring a certain number of runs in the remaining deliveries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 4: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;He belted two huge sixers, but&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;This part of the sentence is &lt;strong&gt;grammatically correct&lt;/strong&gt;. It indicates that the person hit two sixes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;A recent research have underlined&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The error lies in the subject-verb agreement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;The verb&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;have&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;does not agree with its singular subject &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;research&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Research&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;, which is an uncountable noun, should be referred to in the third person singular and matched with a singular verb&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;has&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; instead of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;have&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Thus, the correct phrase should be &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;A recent research has underlined&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence: &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A recent research has underlined&lt;/strong&gt; the relevance of media theory and quantitative empirical approach.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; are both grammatically sound and convey particular concepts correctly in the context of the sentence. The phrase as a whole, &amp;quot;the relevance of media theory and quantitative empirical approach&amp;quot;, is well-phrased and does not contain any grammatical inaccuracies.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;, which suggests that there is &amp;#39;No error&amp;#39;, is incorrect because we have identified a clear error in subject-verb agreement in &amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the use of &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Mohan&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Here possessive case &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Mohan&amp;#39;s&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; will be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Parallelism will be followed before and after&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;as well as&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;Her&amp;quot; is used in possessive case, so &amp;quot;Mohan&amp;quot; will also be used in possessive case i.e. &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Mohan&amp;#39;s&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, option 2 is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;For her sake as well as &lt;strong&gt;Mohan&amp;#39;s&lt;/strong&gt; I hoped fervently that she might get a job.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Parallelism is the use of similar words, phrases, clauses, sentence structure, or other grammatical elements to emphasize similar ideas in an impactful way in a sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It adds balance to the sentence structure and helps create coherent and consistent content.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;My English professor told me&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;to revise&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;my assignment and&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;to pay&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;attention.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The primary issue in the sentence is the use of the phrase &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;so much&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; instead of &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;so many&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Carts&amp;quot; is a plural countable noun and should be paired with &amp;quot;many&amp;quot; instead of &amp;quot;much.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct phrase should be &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;so many&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; ensuring grammatical correctness and clarity.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, the error is located in &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt; of the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;I saw &lt;strong&gt;so many of those&lt;/strong&gt; peasant carts in your yard.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1: &amp;quot;of those peasant&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part of the sentence is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: &amp;quot;No error&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This would be the correct option if there were no mistakes in the sentence, but there is an error in Option 3.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: &amp;quot;carts in your yard.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part of the sentence is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;(b)&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;i.e.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;this part of the sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;has an error&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, the use of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;on&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;incorrect&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;on&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;supported by, fixed to, or touching something&lt;/strong&gt;. (किसी&amp;nbsp;वस्&amp;zwj;तु पर, के ऊपर)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;gap&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in the sentence&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;indicates&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;an empty space in something or between two things&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;preposition &amp;#39;in&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; should be used &lt;strong&gt;in place of&lt;/strong&gt; the &lt;strong&gt;preposition &amp;#39;on&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;preposition &amp;#39;in&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;inside or to a position inside a particular area or object&lt;/strong&gt;. (अंदर या किसी क्षेत्र या वस्&amp;zwj;तु के भीतर कोई स्थिति में, के अंदर)&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Vishnu was trying to pass &lt;strong&gt;through the gap in&lt;/strong&gt; the fence when he tore his shirt&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

