&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;I might watch this programme. It&amp;#39;s supposed to be very interesting.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A: &amp;quot;I might watch&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part of the sentence is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B: &amp;quot;this programme.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part of the sentence is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C: &amp;quot;It&amp;#39;s supposed to be very interesting.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This part of the sentence is grammatically correct and does not require any changes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No error&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This would be the correct option as there are no mistakes in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;signs of robust growth despite their one month age&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;one month age&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is incorrect because it lacks a hyphen between &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;one&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;month&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; when used as a compound adjective.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct form should be &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;one-month age&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; to properly modify the noun &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;age&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When compound adjectives precede a noun, they are usually hyphenated to clarify that the words are functioning together as an adjective.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, omitting &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;one month&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; can make the sentence more concise, e.g., &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;despite their age&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The newest additions to the garden, the plants in the greenhouse, are merely a month old and are already showing&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;signs of robust growth despite their &lt;strong&gt;one-month age&lt;/strong&gt;/&lt;strong&gt;age&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The phrase &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;the plants in the greenhouse&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is grammatically correct and properly identifies the location of the plants without any errors.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The segment &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;are merely a month old and are already showing&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; correctly describes the age of the plants and their developmental progress.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;The newest additions to the garden&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; correctly identifies the subject of the sentence, which is the plants recently added to the garden.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;lsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part B&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rsquo;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;&quot; /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The above sentence is grammatically incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;part B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The above sentence is an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;example of an article&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;An&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;article is a word&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;that is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;used to indicate that a noun is a noun without describing it&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the general rule,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;we do not use articles&lt;/strong&gt; when the &lt;strong&gt;nouns we are using refer to abstract ideas&lt;/strong&gt;. Often &lt;strong&gt;we use abstract nouns&lt;/strong&gt; for this, but not always.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Without &lt;strong&gt;creativity&lt;/strong&gt; we would have no art. (correct)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Without &lt;strong&gt;a creativity&lt;/strong&gt; we would have no art.&lt;/span&gt; (incorrect)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;According to the explanation given above, &amp;lsquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;bravery&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rsquo; is the correct use in place of &amp;ldquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;a bravery&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;He showed great &lt;strong&gt;bravery &lt;/strong&gt;in the face of danger.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
